  <!-- ABOUT HOSHIZAKI -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <h2>Who Hoshizaki is — and why the Alliance matters in LA</h2>
      <p>
        Hoshizaki Corporation started in 1947 in Toyoake, Aichi — a Japanese ice-machine specialist that grew into a
        global commercial foodservice manufacturer. Today the Hoshizaki Group runs 46 affiliated companies worldwide
        with more than 10,000 employees. The US operation, Hoshizaki America, is headquartered in Peachtree City, Georgia,
        with manufacturing plants in Georgia and Arkansas and — this matters — <b>a California parts warehouse that cuts
        LA parts lead times dramatically</b> compared to brands shipping from the East Coast only.
      </p>
      <p>
        The bigger story for LA operators is the Hoshizaki Alliance. What started as Hoshizaki ice and refrigeration
        expanded through acquisitions: <b>Jackson Warewashing Systems</b> (commercial dishwashers, acquired from Manitowoc
        in 2013, Kentucky-based), <b>Lancer Worldwide</b> (beverage dispensers), <b>Fogel Group</b> (refrigeration),
        <b>Hoshizaki Macom</b> (Latin America foodservice), and most recently <b>Structural Concepts</b> (food display
        and merchandising refrigeration, 2025). All six operate as independent brands but share parent ownership, engineering
        standards, and distribution. Both Hoshizaki America and Jackson Warewashing won the 2024 ENERGY STAR Partner of the
        Year award — unusual for two companies in the same corporate family.
      </p>
      <p>
        At Same Day Appliance Repair Los Angeles the Alliance is why we put Hoshizaki at the top of our commercial brand
        stack. A sushi bar in Sawtelle, a Korean BBQ house in Koreatown, or a poke shop in the Arts District is likely
        running Hoshizaki ice plus Jackson dishwashers — and when one goes down, the operator doesn't want to call two
        service companies. One tech, one invoice, shared parts logistics.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT WE SERVICE -->
  <section id="services" class="section alt">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>Hoshizaki equipment we service in LA</h2>
      <p class="intro">
        Hoshizaki is a full commercial equipment brand — not just ice. Here's what our techs show up for across the
        Alliance ecosystem:
      </p>
      <div class="model-grid">
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Hoshizaki Ice Machines</h3>
          <p>KM-series cube ice machines (100–2,500 lb/day range, crescent cube shape), F-series flake ice machines (for sushi,
          seafood, poke, produce display), DCM-series ice & water dispensers, FM-series mini cubes, countertop ice makers.
          CleanCycle12 self-cleaning circuit is the proprietary Hoshizaki quality angle — and the most common commercial ice
          machine repair diagnostic target when ice production drops. Our techs service the full Hoshizaki ice machine lineup
          across LA.</p>
          <a href="/brands/hoshizaki-ice-machine-repair/" class="card-link">→ Hoshizaki ice machine repair</a>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Hoshizaki Commercial Refrigeration</h3>
          <p>HR-series reach-in refrigerators, HF-series reach-in freezers, HCR/HCF griddle-station units, Steelheart
          heavy-duty line for casinos and high-volume kitchens, Economy Series for entry-level builds. Japanese-engineered
          antimicrobial stainless, low-velocity airflow for tight temperature control.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Jackson Dishwashers</h3>
          <p>NXP high-temp and low-temp undercounters, Avenger door-type dishmachines, conveyor-type (flight-type for high
          volume), glasswashers. Kentucky-manufactured since the Hoshizaki acquisition in 2013, energy-efficient enough to
          share the 2024 ENERGY STAR Partner of the Year award with Hoshizaki America.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Lancer Beverage Dispensers</h3>
          <p>IBD Bold 30i beverage dispensers, soda fountain systems, post-mix and pre-mix equipment. Often paired with
          Hoshizaki ice in fast-casual and convenience-store builds.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>CleanCycle12 Self-Cleaning</h3>
          <p>Hoshizaki's proprietary self-cleaning circuit on KM and DCM ice machines. When ice production drops or the
          unit throws a CleanCycle fault, the usual suspects are the water solenoid, the sensor package, or scale on the
          probe assembly. LA hard-water service accelerates scale buildup; we service this regularly.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>F-series Flake for Sushi & Seafood</h3>
          <p>F-801 through F-2000 flakers sit at the heart of LA's Japanese, Korean, and seafood restaurant cluster. When
          a flaker goes down during service, display cases turn into liabilities within an hour. Our techs carry auger
          motors, water regulators, and thermistor probes for the common F-series sizes.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Structural Concepts Merchandising</h3>
          <p>Open-air food display cases, grab-and-go merchandisers, hot-food wells. Joined Hoshizaki Alliance in 2025.
          Heavy LA install base in hotels, cafeterias, hospitals, and grocery foodservice.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>DCM-series Ice & Water Dispensers</h3>
          <p>Combined ice and water dispensers for hotel beverage stations, employee break rooms, and fitness-facility
          hydration points. Common failures: solenoid on the water path, user-interface board, and dispenser chute
          alignment.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Ice Machine Maintenance</h3>
          <p>LA hard water accelerates scale on every commercial ice machine brand — Hoshizaki included. We handle
          descaling, sanitizing, water-filter replacement, condenser cleaning, and ice production testing on regular
          maintenance schedules. Properly maintained Hoshizaki ice machines run cleaner, produce more ice per kWh, and
          stretch the life of the compressor and evaporator plate significantly.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

