      <h2>Hoshizaki Alliance — fact check</h2>
      <p>
        LA foodservice operators sometimes hear conflicting information about Hoshizaki's corporate structure, especially
        around Jackson. Here's the clean version:
      </p>
      <ul class="check-list">
        <li><b>Parent:</b> Hoshizaki Corporation (Japan, Toyoake Aichi, founded 1947). US subsidiary Hoshizaki America
          in Peachtree City, Georgia.</li>
        <li><b>Alliance members:</b> Hoshizaki America + Jackson Warewashing Systems + Lancer Worldwide + Fogel Group +
          Hoshizaki Macom + Structural Concepts.</li>
        <li><b>Jackson history:</b> Kentucky-based, previously owned by Manitowoc, acquired by Hoshizaki USA Holdings
          in 2013. All current production is US-manufactured.</li>
        <li><b>Structural Concepts:</b> newest Alliance addition (2025) — food display and merchandising refrigeration.</li>
        <li><b>California warehouse:</b> Hoshizaki runs a West Coast parts distribution hub. For LA kitchens, this
          typically means next-day parts on common KM and HR items vs. cross-country shipping.</li>
        <li><b>Global scale:</b> Hoshizaki Group = 46 affiliated companies, 10,000+ employees worldwide.</li>
        <li><b>Not Ali Group, not Middleby, not Welbilt:</b> Hoshizaki is independent of the three big US commercial
          holding groups. Parts channels, service networks, and engineering are Hoshizaki-internal.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHY OPERATORS CALL US -->
  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>Why LA operators call us for Hoshizaki and Jackson service</h2>
      <div class="why-grid">
        <div>
          <h4>Alliance package in one visit</h4>
          <p>If your kitchen runs Hoshizaki ice, Hoshizaki reach-in refrigeration, and Jackson dishwashers, we service
          all three on the same ticket. One tech, one invoice, shared parts sourcing.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>Flake-ice priority dispatch</h4>
          <p>F-series flakers down during service at a sushi bar or poke shop is a business-interruption emergency. We
          prioritize Japanese-concept restaurants in Sawtelle, Little Tokyo, and West LA for same-day ice machine repair.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>California parts pipeline</h4>
          <p>Hoshizaki's California warehouse is a real advantage. We source through authorized channels — common KM
          solenoids, float switches, and CleanCycle sensor assemblies arrive in one to two days instead of a week.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>Hard-water scale expertise on commercial ice machines</h4>
          <p>LA's water profile is brutal on every commercial ice machine. We see the scale patterns week after week
